flunomide''s active metabolite from plasma, which otherwise may take up to two years.', 'Synergism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/128480/', '[1] "Product Information. Arava (leflunomide)." Hoechst Marion-Roussel Inc, Kansas City, MO.[2] "Product Information. Aubagio (teriflunomide)." Genzyme Corporation, Cambridge, MA.[3] EMEA "EMEA public statement on leflunomide (ARAVA) - severe and serious hepatic reactions. Available from URL: http://www.eudra.org/emea.html." ([1999 Sept 2]):', 1767365207);
